  <div class="main content-container" role="main">
    
      <div class="article-teaser">
        Working with the Rail Delivery Group, we run an ongoing survey on Travelcards to help us understand how they are used and to raise money for charity.
        
      </div>
    
    
      <p>We distribute thousands of Travelcard surveys every year for customers to record their journeys on public transport. We can't get this data from Oyster records alone because customers using Travelcards on Oyster don't necessarily need to touch in and out when travelling within their ticket's zones.</p>

<p>For each diary completed and returned to us, we donate &pound;2 split equally between our four nominated registered charities:</p>

<ul>
	<li><a href="http://www.asthma.org.uk/">Asthma UK</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://www.rspb.org.uk">The Royal Society for the Protection of Birds</a></li>
	<li><a href="https://www.mariecurie.org.uk/">Marie Curie</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://www.citizensadvice.org.uk/">Citizens Advice Bureau</a></li>
</ul>

<p>Customers have helped us raise more than &pound;489,775 as of May 2019. Our latest donation shared &pound;1,854 among our nominated charities.</p>

<p>You may receive a Travelcard diary through the post or by email, or one of our surveyors may offer you a diary at a station.</p>

<p>The diaries are simple to fill in and free to return, see below for more detail on completing a diary.</p>

<p>Every diary we get back is useful, so thanks to all of you who have helped out with the survey so far.</p>

<p><strong>Completing diaries</strong></p>

<p>When completing diaries, please remember to:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Record all trips, including return trips</li>
	<li>Record trips on London Overground and TfL Rail as 'Rail'</li>
	<li>Record trips on different modes separately, for example if you take the Tube to Finsbury Park and then change to National Rail, record the trips as separate entries on the diary</li>
</ul>
      
           
      
